                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/441: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-11T09:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1917, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 3.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My telegram November 16, 8 p.m. Conference meets January 5th. Japanese Government
                    suggests that to expedite matters preliminary agreement be made to the effect
                    that the average value of merchandise during 1991, 12 and 13 be taken as the
                    basis of customs revision. The French Legation and Belgian propose that the
                    conference take action by a majority vote. Their motive is to avoid possible
                    obstruction by any neutral. I have the honor to ask your instructions on both
                    matters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
